an peasantry. Drawn from previously unavailable and in many cases unknown archives, these harrowing documents provide the first unimpeded view of the experience of the peasantry during the years 1927-1930.The book, the first of four in the series, covers the background of collectivization, its violent implementation, and the mass peasant revolt that ensued. For its insights into the horrific fate of the Russian peasantry and into Stalin's dictatorship, The War Against the Peasantry takes its place an as unparalleled resource.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCollectivization of agriculturexSourcesxHistoryxSoviet Union. 0aCollectivization of agriculturezSoviet UnionxHistoryvSources. 0aPeasantsxSourcesxHistoryxSoviet Union. 0aPeasantszSoviet UnionxHistoryvSources. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aDanilov, V. P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIvnitskii, N. A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKozlov, Denis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShabad, Steven1 aViola, Lynne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300127829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300127829.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles